# iyt_how_i_messed_up_my_university_experience
AKA Advice I would give to my 18 year old self

# 18 year old
- take a gap year
- really think about if you want to go to uni for 3 years.
- you are too half-in-half-out with uni, so decide properly and test out the "learning on my own" and "solo game dev" idea here and now
- 

# sucesses
- 

# uni

## focus on the work not the identity
- take medication
- I was a "good student" but a poor performer
- I had days where there were 8 hours of lectures and the rest of the days were 2 hours
- some of the lecturers had terrible lecturing skills, really bad. Some lecturers would just be reading a pdf. Some lecturers didn't show up once when we were timetabled for a lecture.
- Go to lectures if the lecturer was good, and there wasn't a million lectures that day
- 50% rule. 50% of my time should be doing mathematics i.e. problem sheets, so about 4 hours a day.
- when it gets too exhausting that day, do other activities like gym
- make notes that are "proprietary" (only you can understand as they are so half-written) easy to understand by you come exam time and quick. Don't try to make beautiful, readable, clear notes that take the whole day to write out. Doing problem sheets until it's muscle memory is more important than this point.
- writing notes online (vim) has been fine for me, paper notes would work okay.

- Spend term time optimising learning, and spend holiday time trying to become an algorithm of getting 100% in an exam the easiest way, regardless of if you are just memorising answer booklets.
- get an internship 

